instance twinning_time_scale : DTDFVocab:TimeScale [
    base:desc "Temporal synchronization is achieved through a shared clock across the Digital Twin system, with a required accuracy of 100 ms to satisfy safety‑critical vehicular application standards. Devices perform computation offloading only when their local clocks are synchronized within this bound. ROS2 packages utilize DDS time sources, and the system execution aims to maintain a maximum 100 ms latency between physical sensor events and their digital twin representations."
